text: Joseph S. Miller was a Commissioner of Internal Revenue at the Internal Revenue Service in the United States. His state was West Virginia. Miller served as IRS Commissioner from March 20, 1885 to March 20, 1889 and from April 19, 1893 to November 26, 1896. A photograph of Miller by Charles Milton Bell is held at the Library of Congress. == References == Category:Commissioners of Internal Revenue Category:Year of birth missing Category:Year of death missing
